inn1.comm: full in length on the off and middle stump line, and Simmons gets right behind the line to defend to the off side of the pitch.
this one climbs from short of length, a surprised Simmons adjusts by taking the bottom-hand of the handle and stabs the ball to backward square-leg
cuts in to the off stump line, the batsman gets back to jab it towards back ward point. The ball rolls away slowly and the batsmen rush across
wayward wide delivery outside off and the ump Ashoka de Silva extends his arms.
lovely delivery; bouncing away from short of length and in the zone outside off, Simmons pokes at it and the ball rushes past the edge. No ball, though.
Has a big slog across the line at this free hit delivery -full and well outside off- and the edge flies to third man.. Umar Akmal runs all the way back and clangs it. Not that it mattered
gets behind the line to defend this to the off
pushes this wide of mid-on for a single. Ugly sound off the bat. a dead Tuk. change of bat please?!
Whack! He hasn''t changed the piece of wood but connected superbly this time. Lovely woody sound as he unfurled the cut shot. The ball flew over point. too short from the debutant
full in length, around off stump line, pushed back down the track
short and wide. Nerves I guess.
from wide of the crease, this angles in, moves past the prod and hits the pad. High and going down the leg side
again that dead-wood sound as he stabs this to cover. hmm
a loud cry for lbw but ump Malcolm isn't impressed much. It cut in from outside off stump and moved in to hit the pad. High and going down
again, angles this one in, fuller in length, again Smith is caught on the shuffle and the ball rolls away behind square-leg
leans forward to stab this one to cover.
gets behind the line to punch this one out to the off side
For a moment, I thought Smith was late in getting forward to the full-length delivery but he adjusted and creamed this full delivery through cover point
Bosh! This one was the short delivery and Smith was ready for it; he got into position, fetched it from around off and pulled it through midwicket. Wahab is being looted for runs here
full in length, tilting away slightly and Smith gets back to defend it to the off side
this one kicks up from short of length, around off, Smith takes off his bottom-hand of the handle and jabs it back down the track.
full in length and outside leg stump for a wide
angling away from Simmons who tries to run it past the slips, down to thirdman, but makes no contact
on the leg side, Simmons misses out on an opportunity to leg-glance a boundary there; the ball rolls off the pad
in the zone outside off stump, pushed out to point
runs this down to third man for a single
shuffles across, opens his bat-face to cover for the away movement and dabs it to left of backward point
another single down to third man. he is angling it across the batsman
a full delivery, almost yorker length and Smith is down on the ground. He tried to flick it, was not in balance and slipped and fell.
full in length on the off stump line, eased to mid-off
works this length delivery to square-leg. Again, the front leg comes across a touch and he isn't in great balance when he plays that shot to the leg side
full and outside off this time and Smith, who favours the off side, pushes this out to cover
gets forward to tap this full-length delivery to mid-on
full in length, gentle seam-up delivery around off, pushed out to cover
lands outside leg stump, on a length, and moves to leg stump line. Again, Simmons misses out on the leg-glance,, the ball rolls out behind square-leg
goes down the track and the bowler tucks him on the leg stump line., Smith isn't strong there and ends up jabbing it to square-leg
tries to tuck him up again on the leg line but ends up pushing it down leg side for a wide
cuts into middle and leg line, Smith stays back to clip it through backward square-leg for couple of runs.
slower, moving into leg and middle, tapped to square-leg
again that problem surfaces when he tries to play it to the leg side. No balance and he ends up stabbing at it and the ball rolls out to point
from round the stumps, just outside off stump, pushed out to short extra cover
lovely turning off break! It drifted into middle stump line and turned away past the defensive push.
gets back to cut this to point

Lbw! Ashoka de Silva takes a while but nods his head eventually and raises the finger. It landed on a length on the  off stump line and went on with the arm. Smith pushed outside the line and the ball went through bat and pad gap to hit him right in front of middle. That's out. Smith has a chat with his partner before he eventually turned and left. wonder what was that about
slip and leg slip in place and Bravo pushes it to covers. The fielder rushes in quickly and throws to the keeper who says, "Kya baat hai sir?!"
leans well forward to defend this to the off side
shuffles right across the stumps to defend to the off side
on the pads, glances this to fine-leg for a single
in the zone outside off stump and this just about tilts away after landing and Bravo is beaten, pushing inside the line
shuffles across to defend this to the off side
steers this to backward point and there is a direct hit at the non-striker's end but Simmons was home
in the corridor outside off stump, left alone
gets back to dab this off break to the leg side
from over the wicket, turns in from outside off, nudged to the leg side
and again, gets back to work this to midwicket
slower, flighted and Simmons leans forward to defend
stretches forward to defend this to the off side
flighted full delivery, tapped to mid-on
on the off stump line, pushed out to cover
hurls this wide outside off stump. Again that release going awry because of that action
fuller and closer to the off stump line, guided down to third man
Simmons goes down town. He played similar shots in the Twenty20 game. He leaned forward to lift the length delivery up and over mid-on
short in length just outside off and Bravo punches it to right of mid-off
gets back to clip this length delivery to square-leg
in the corridor outside off and Bravo is beaten, pushing inside the line
clips the first ball of the bowling powerplay to deep square-leg region
leans across to push it to cover
on the middle stump line, Bravo eases it to covers
lands on middle and leg and turns into middle- he is bowling from round the stumps- defended on the front foot

stifled shout for a catch. It was the off break just outside off, and Bravo pushed inside the line and the ball turned past the bat. The keeper went up before putting his hand up, suggesting there was no edge
leans forward to defend to the off
cuts in from just outside off stump, from round the stumps now, punched out to point
again from round the stumps, around that off stump line, defended of the back foot
shuffles across to the off and defends to the off

Bravo tries to break free of the shackles and takes the risk: he tries to punch on the up and mistimed it as the bat-face turned at point of impact and the ball wobbled away in the air to right of mid-off
dabs this to the square-leg
full in length outside off stump, pushed out to covers
just short of length, cut away to sweeper cover
leans forward to ease this to long-on
backs away to carve this to the off side
works this wide of midwicket for a single
on the middle stump line, Bravo backs away, realises the ball is skidding on to the middle stump, and he adjusts to jab it away to the off
cuts this one away to deep point region
from over the wicket and this one turns big! It landed around leg and spun away sharply, Bravo let that one alone
supah! this one turns from the leg and is a lot closer to the off and Bravo pokes at it and is beaten.
beaten again! This one is slower and slightly wide, Bravo was backing away, and then tried to lunge out to cut and misses
Ajmal continues to tease and harass Bravo. He is beaten again, this time trying to defend on the front foot but the ball spins past the edge
leans forward to defend this one back down the track
What does he have to do to get the edge?! Unlucky hafeez. Again, Bravo is beaten, pushing inside the line. The ball lands around leg and turns right across Bravo
turns in from outside off, pushed away on the front foot
stays back to cut this one to the off
moves down the track, doesn' t reach the pitch of the ball and jabs it to the leg side
gets forward and across and works with the turn past square-leg
from round the stumps, on the middle stump line, Bravo backs away to punch it out to sweeper cover
gets back to tap this off break to the leg side
from over the wicket., turning from outside leg , Bravo defends on the back foot

stays back to dab this to short midwicket. again, this one turned from outside leg. He beat the bat last over when he started it to turn from the leg stump. So far, this over, he has landed em outside leg
outside leg again. spins in., defended to the off
And here we go. This time he lands it around leg and gets it to turn across a bewildered Bravo who stabs it off the edge through gully
stays back to punch it to short extra cover
lands outside leg, shorter and flatter, punched out to sweeper cover
from round the stumps, pushed out to short extra cover
break free! he gets outside leg and cuts this off break from the off stump line to deep point region
on the leg and middle line, nudged to square-leg
flighted on the off and middle line and Simmons goes for the big slog sweep on a bent knee but edges it to his pad. He is itching to break free here
And he does it this time. he rushed down the track and heaves the length delivery just wide, to the right, of the deep midwicket fielder. One bounce and over the ropes
very full delivery around off, eased through covers for couple of runs
on the middle stump line, full, Bravo pushes it rather tentatively to cover point

The doosra, outside off and Simmons lets it go. He picked it off the turf I reckon as he hung out his bat initially but the short-of-length delivery allowed him to adjust and removed his bat from the line of trouble
stretches well forward to defend to the off side
gets back this time to steer this through point
troubled by the doosra! Wicked delivery, It landed around leg and turned the other way, Bravo was looking to cut and to his horror the ball came in to tuck him up. It went off the pad
edged but short of the diving first slip. Bravo, again, lunges out very very tentatively and pokes at the off break. The ball goes off the edge but falls short of the fielder
leans forward to squeeze this to point
gets forward to defend to the off side
looks like he was about to sweep but when he saw  that ball was well outside off, he adjusted and steered it to backward point
again, manages to only tap it to backward point
full delivery, Simmons almost yorks himself as the bill dips on him and jabs it to the off side
quicker, skids outside off, pushed out wide of cover fielder

Ump Malcolm, just like Ashoka earlier, takes a while before raising the finger. It was the doosra that landed around off and swerved away. Simmons leaned forward to defend and pushed inside the line. There must have been a thin edge as it went through to the delighted Salman. They appealed. They appealed again. The fatal finger shot up.
another doosra but this time the batsman picks it and defends to the off
the off break this time and the batsman lunges forward and across; the ball turns past the bat and bounds off the pad
No one is reading his doosras! Wicked delivery! This one breaks away from the off stump and the batsman is beaten comprehensively
When in doubt either sweep or lunge out completely. he chooses to do the latter and takes this on the pad
Samuels picks the doosra this time and defends. Perhaps the length - it was slightly short of length- allowed him to adjust
from round the stumps, leg break outside off, tapped to cover
turns in to the middle stump line, worked away to fine-leg region
flighted full outside off, pushed to right of short extra cover for a quick single
gets back to nudge this to square-leg region
from round the stumps, full and outside off, dabbed to point
this one broke away after landing outside off, short in length ,cut away to sweeper cover
gets back to punch it through cover point
gets back and across to push it back down the track
doosra but on the leg and middle line, nurdled to backward square-leg fielder
off break this time, quickish from outside off, Samuels gets back to defend

quicker one, pushed out to left of cover and Afridi, as is his wont, runs across the ball and fields it on his right side. he rarely stops them with his left .. likes to run right across and stop it with his throwing arm
presses back to push this to short cover
around that off stump line, eased away to backward point.
gets forward to work this to short midwicket. Strangulation by spin on
around the off stump line, on a length ,defended on the front foot
lands on the leg and middle line and turns into middle, defended on the back foot
googly that  skids in from around off stump, the batsman pushes outside the line and is struck high on the pad
another tight over of spin. This is pushed quietly to covers
Short and outside off, cut away wide of sweeper cover
short in length outside off, cut away to sweeper cover
gets behind the line to nudge this to midwicket
stays back to push it out to the off side, the non striker thinks about the single and Umar Akmal fires a quick throw

Samuels is run out!  Samuels ran Simmons out in the T20. And yes, folks no need to mention that Lara dismissal please! It rolled off the pad to say leg slip region. Samuels set off for the run and so did Bravo, who then changes his mind. Samuels then turns back and has a good view of Salman firing a direct hit. Out by the proverbial mile
on the pads, nudged away for a run
stays behind the line to defend
gets a single down to short fine-leg
gets forward to work it to midwicket
presses back to glide this to backward point
in the zone outside off, angling away and he is beaten, pushing inside the line
shortish delivery on leg and middle, pulled down to fine-leg for a single
stays back to defend to the leg side
on a length on the middle, tucked away through backward square-leg
punches this through to sweeper cover
slower one, full and outside off, sliced away to deep cover and they come back for the second run
on the middle stump line, worked around to short midwicket
from round the stumps, leg break from outside off, defended back down the track
googly from round the stumps, tapped to the off side
fuller, outside off, flicked away for a single
skids on to middle and leg, clipped to square-leg
loopy flighted delivery around off, squeezed out to short point for a quick single
just outside off stump, pats it down to backward point
on the middle stump line, cut away to sweeper cover where Ajmal mops up
turns in from outside off, from over the wicket, defended on the back foot
stays back to punch this to the right of Hafeez who fumbles
on the middle and off line, pushed out to right of cover
gets well back to create some room and punches this from middle to long-off
leans forward to tap it to left of cover and again, Afridi runs right around it, takes it on his right hand and throws. But the non-striker was home by then.
pushed away to the off side for a single
leans forward to dab this to the off
turns this wide of midwicket for a single
shortish delivery, pulled but straight to short midwicket
slower, on a length, eased to midwicket for a single! Afridi had just taken out that fielder
gets forward to stab this back to Afridi
turns in slowly from outside off, pushed out to short midwicket
stays back to push to right of Bravo
on the off and middle line ,steered to point region for a single
flighted on a length around legs, tickled past square-leg
leans forward to ease it to long-off
leans forward to nudge this to short midwicket
punches this through to wide long-off region
leg break from round the stumps, turned to square-leg
off break this time, pushed out to point region.
the googly this time! Supah stuff from Afridi. Bravo defended this to the off
turns this in to middle stump line, worked through midwicket
from over the stumps now, skids in from outside off, cut away to sweeper cover
drop-and-run into the covers from Edwards, they charge through for a quick single
Hafeez comes round the wicket to Bravo, who flicks him wristily out towards deep midwicket, and they're back for the second
plenty of revs on this one, and though there's not much flight the ball still drifts noticeably through the air. Defended to off
Bravo steps back and chops down to cover point, but can't find the gap
speared down towards leg stump this time, and Bravo nudges him fine for a single
Edwards, with a very open stance to the spinners - his body almost facing mid-off - flicks a darted delivery past a diving short fine leg for a single
full on off stump from round the wicket, pushed to mid-off
a quick single! Edwards nudged it right between the cover and mid-off fielders without much power but with just the right placement for the sneakiest of singles
hurled down the leg side by Khan
another very tight run, Bravo dropping the ball into the covers and just setting off ... the through is just wide, he would've been gone by an inch or two

Edwards is no Chanderpaul but has a similarly crab-like demeanour at the crease, shuffling across from a front on stance and chopping this awkwardly down in defence. Awkward but effective, West Indies will be hoping
pushed into the covers
full to finish, and Edwards drives without much timing to mid-on
turns in from outside off, shoved away to long-off for a single
rushes down the track, looking for the big hit, and mistimes it but. The ball falls short of long-on
slower, spins in from outside off, squeezed out to backward point
from round the stumps to the lefty, pushed out to point for another single.
on the pads, swatted to fine-leg
around off stump line, tapped to backward point
from round the stumps, on a length on the middle, turned to midwicket
shortish delivery, on the rib cage, turned down to fine-leg
fullihs, on the off, driven to long-on. A mistimed drive.
short of length around off, nudged to right of backward point for a quick single
around the off stump, tapped to covers. He now goes for some gardening down the track
full and angling away from Kirk who slashes it to third man
loopy off break, full and on middle and off, the batsman stabs it of the inner edge to his pad
slowish off break this time, Kirk sets up for a big hit before he checks his shot and dabs it to point
just outside leg stump, wristed to left of Afridi at midwicket
a sharply turning doosra! and Kirk just about holds his bat inside the line
Another fab doosra! Kirk has a lame, dangerous, poke at it and is beaten
gets back to dab this off break to the leg side
low full toss and wide down the leg side. Wahab's probs with wides continue
on the off stump line, on a length, tapped to the on side of the pitch
More wides down the leg side.
leans forward to drive but mistimes it through mid-on for a single
angles away from Kirk who can't get bat to ball
And again. A pretty lame effort to cut this time. A gentle waft
full and well outside off, reaches out to drive it away from his body to covers
outside off stump line, shuffles across to shove it to long-off
turns in to off stump line, cut away to sweeper cover
turns across from outside leg, defended to the off
tossed up full around off and Bravo lofts it over his partner
clips this doosra to short fine-leg
turns from outside leg, Bravo stabs it to the off side
spins across Bravo who steers it towards backward point for a quick single
Yet another wide. Again, slipping down leg side. Wahab shakes his head as he walks back
length delivery around off, pushed to right of cover. Overthrows as the ball misses the stumps at the non-striker's end. No one there to back-up and Shehzad has a wild throw at it.
gets forward to push it to mid-off
slower one, on a length, around off, steered past backward point
Hmm .. poor stuff from Wahab. This one is a wide down the leg side.
Kirk holes out to deep midwicket. He walked down the track, looking for the slog, Wahab hurled it shorter and Kirk top edged the pull
Oh dear. What a mess. The release goes all wrong and the ball flies way down the leg side and Salman does a very good job to cut off 4 byes with a dive
gets forward to push it to cover
short in length, rolls off the pad to backward square-leg
slightly short of length, cut away to sweeper cover
leans forward to defend the leg break to the off side
gets back to punch it to right of extra cover where Umar makes a tumbling save
drifts to the pads, nudged to short fine-leg
on the pads again, flicked away past square-leg this time
full delivery again on the pads, turned through  backward square-leg
low full toss on the middle, pushed to right of mid-off for a single. That's Darren's fifty. He raises his bat
length delivery on the off, pushed to left of cover where Afridi stops and throws at non-striker's end. Darren had stepped out for the run but got back in time
punches this length delivery on the up but that's not an easy task on this sluggish track. he mistimes it to mid-on
tries to the slower off cutter and ends up bowling a wide down the leg side
short in length around off, punched away to mid-off for a quick single.
short of length, swatted away wide of Afridi at midwicket
slower one, the cutter, on leg and middle line, squeezed down to fine-leg region
tries to go for a lofted off drive but mistimes it; it lands safely between long-on and long-off
rotates the strike over with a dab to midwicket
skids away from Darren who is beaten by the away movement. he pushes inside the line.
long hop outside off, cut away to sweeper cover. Just a single.
on the pads, turned through midwicket and they turn back for the second
around the off stump line, eased down to long-off
from round the stumps, full delivery outside off, Dwayne plays a stylish square drive but can't beat point
shout for lbw but that was going down leg. It was from round the stumps and the ball moved in past the attempted flick and hit the pad. Hawk eye suggesting it would have clipped the leg stump
full delivery, from over the wicket this time, Darren goes hard into the drive but doesn't find any timing. The ball rolls to extra cover
tries the yorker, ends up as a low dipping full delivery, pushed out to wide mid-on
First boundary in a long long time. It was the slower one, a short one at that, and Darren flat-bats it, slaps it, over wide long-on!
suddenly, the dam has cracked open. Darren lifts this full-length delivery up and over extra cover
on the pads, tickled to short fine-leg fielder
lands on the middle and turns, Darren adjusts and works it to point
stays round the stumps to Dwayne as well and bowls it full on leg and middle, tucked to midwicket
quicker one outside off, driven but straight to cover
slightly slower, shorter in length, cut to left of extra cover where Shehzad makes a tumbling save and seems to have hurt himself in the process
leans forward to defend to the off side
fullish outside off, Dwayne shuffles across and whips it away to long-off
tries to drill it through the off but edges it to the leg side, behind the stumps, for a single
And back to regular programming: A wide way outside off stump
Good diving catch from the captain. Bravo scooped a low dipping full delivery towards cover where Afridi reacted quickly to lunge forward to take it
short in length, on the middle and leg, rolls out to the leg side
fullish outside leg, Darren goes outside leg and tries to whip it away. It goes off his pad to the keeper. No ball, though Afridi looks so so disappointed.

Darren is run out! It was fullish, hint of inswing, and he drove it to left of long-off and they try to take on the throw, Wonderfully accurate throw by Shehzad from the deep and Salman does the rest. Run out on the free-hit delivery. Not too smart.
Oh dear. What is happening. Afridi has his hands on his hips. yet another wide down the leg side.
on the middle and off line, tapped to the on side.
turns in from outside off, punched out to cover
and again.
skids on quickly this time and Sammy can't connect with his cut
Thump! The doosra this time but too short and Sammy retreated inside the crease and slapped it over covers
fuller this time, again a doosra, and Sammy is beaten, looking to defend
another one that goes away, steered to backward point
length delivery on the off, pushed out to covers
shortish ball just down the leg side. The batsman was trying to paddle it away but missed. It wasn't all that far away from the leg stump.
full in length outside off, run down to third man
slower one, around off, dragged down to deep midwicket
slower one well outside off, close to being called a wide. The batsmen get together for a chat
in the corridor outside off, Baugh tries to steer it to third man but makes no contact
shuffles across and guides it wide of third man
chops this leg break to right of backward point for a single
Bosh! It was a full-length delivery but Sammy backed away and somehow managed to create room and thump it over long-on.
drifts to the pad and Sammy plays that whippy aerial flick that he plays to collect another boundary
stays back to push this to long-off
skids away outside off stump, goes for the cut but misses
big heave! Baugh slams a full delivery to the right of long-off. It bounced just inside the ropes and bounces over.
Here we go again. Waqar Younis and Aquib Javed must be tearing their hair .. wide outside off
low full toss, heaved away, just short of long-off
slightly slower, Baugh goes for the pull but doesn't get any wood on leather
slower one, fullish outside off, driven to deep cover
Killer blow! It lands on the roof beyond midwicket. Stunning strike. He cleared the front foot and smashed this full delivery way over the stands. Wonderful heave-ho! Thunderous wallop
Slasher Sammy! He opens up his stance and crashes a full delivery over extra cover.
And of course there has to be another wide. Else, it won't be normal, would it?

slower one now, dragged through square-leg.. Wide throw and they take the overthrows. Sammy had actually slipped and fallen at the non-striker;s end but that throw allowed him to recover and come back for the extra run
from round the stumps, it breaks away from Baugh who tries the slog sweep but doesn't connect
turns this to short third man to give the strike to Sammy
another doosra, another swing and a miss
tries to heave this to the leg side, misses and collects a leg bye
just outside off stump, from round the stumps, Baugh fails to connect
hmm .. last ball of the innings and he seems to be tired of swinging and missing and so, he taps this one to the off and takes a single

inn2.comm: starts off with a good length delivery outside off and Hafeez goes for an off drive, bat away from the body and he ends up pushing inside the line.
straighter, fuller, on driven to mid-on
full and in the zone outside off, hafeez shoulders arms
drifts to the pads, clipped away for a single.
hits the good length area outside the off stump, defended away to the off side
lovely delivery, sort of holding its line outside off and Shehzad is beaten, poking inside the line
starts off with a mild query for lbw after hitting Hafeez on the pad with a full delivery. Going down leg, though
drags this short around off and hafeez has all the time in the planet to swivel and whack-pull it over midwicket.
Short again. Pulled again. Four again.
ah lovely off drive this time. It was a full delivery outside off and Hafeez leaned across to caress it through extra cover
Finally, on a good length and in the channel outside off, left alone.
hits the good length again, around off, eased to mid-on

Roach does a Sammy. Short ball, of course he has more pace and has hit Ponting with a bouncer but this one didn't have much pace on it and this pitch is pretty slow and Hafeez pulled it just over the leaping midwicket boundary
Pretty! It was a short of length delivery around off stump, Hafeez stood on his toes and creamed it on the up and through cover point. Sweet
in the channel, left alone
length delivery, moving in towards the off stump, defended to the off side
covers the off stump and lets the keeper take this
gets forward to work it off his hips through backward square-leg
leans forward to ease this full delivery to mid-off

cuts in to the middle, dabbed away to short midwicket. he had to play around that front pad that time. It will be worth it for Sammy, and the other bowlers, to keep the incutters going now and then to try get an lbw
again, that front foot comes a tad too much across but he checks it in time and gets the bat around the pad to defend
just outside off this time and hafeez gets forward to defend
on the middle and leg this time and Hafeez works it through midwicket for couple of easy runs
on the middle and off line, nudged to short midwicket
Up and running. Shehzad creams this overpitched delivery outside off through cover point.
hits the good length this time and Shehzad shoulders arms
Fabulicious! It was a short of length delivery outside off and Shehzad played it late, rode the bounce, and punched it so sweetly to left of backward point
on the middle stump this time, turned to midwicket
full in length around off and Shehzad glided forward quickly and caressed it between the bowler and the non-striker. Neatly done
short in length, bounces a bit more, defended to the leg side

Hafeez almost did a Hafeez. He almost gave away his wicket. It was a short of length delivery on the middle and leg and he top-edged a swat-pull and Roach came in from deep backward square-leg and almost got to the ball. It fell just short of him;.
pushes this wide down the leg side for a wide
full in length on the middle and off, defended to the on side
in the channel, Hafeez lets it go through to the keeper
Ah Nice. It was the length delivery that came in to the middle, probably middle and leg, and Hafeez arrested the front-foot movement and clipped it through midwicket
pushes this outside off, left alone
the bouncer, high though, and it flies over the batsman
on a good length around off stump, defended to the on side of the pitch
short in length on the off stump line, defended to the on side
full in length and it tilted away after landing outside off, left alone
slower and further away from the off stump, left alone again
short in length outside off, punched away to covers
It's a maiden over; Shehzad pushes this full delivery to mid-on
the bouncer and Hafeez is quick to get into position to play that pull shot. Nicely done. he got on top of the bounce and hit it down to the ground and to the right of backward square-leg fielder
in the zone outside off and Hafeez shoulders arms.
Delicious cover drive! Fab shot. He leaned forward and across, got close to the full-length delivery and laced it through covers.
just outside off stump, on a good length, defended out to covers
just outside off, from a good length, left alone
short in length outside off and Hafeez plays a neat punchy drive through backward point. Neat and sweet!
moves in towards the off stump, tapped away to mid-on

Bishoo takes out Shehzad! Another lovely leg break, luring Shehzad forward by the flight, before it dipped and turned away from him. Shehzad wasn't looking for the big hit; he didn't throw his wicket; he was just done in by a good delivery. He leaned forward to just defend but dragged his back foot outside the crease and was done in by the flight, loop, and turn. Stumped!
Two slips in place and Bishoo bowls the toppie! nice stuff. The batsman was playing for the turn; there wasn't any but he got an inside edge to the leg side.
